<head>SNOW</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">雪</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">雪</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>WHITE FROZEN RAIN.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The dominant word is xuě 雪.</p>
<p>2. Xiàn 霰 are snowflakes, and the structure of these drew early Chinese attention.</p>
<p>3. Bīng 冰 is ice. See ICE.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>雪</p>
